deck: A weekly British comic for boys which featured war stories. It ran from 1975 to 1988, when the title was merged with Eagle.
description:
Battle was a weekly British publication for boys with stories about war. There were 664* weekly issues (from 1975 to 1988) until the title merged with Eagle (issue 306).

Battle went through several different title changes. Its most radical name change was Battle Action Force, when the comic ran stories featuring the Action Force action figure toy line.

Battle's title changes are:

  • Battle Picture Weekly (From 8 March 1975 to 16 October 1976 - Numbers 1-85)
  • Battle Picture Weekly and Valiant (From 23 October 1976 to 12 November 1977 - Numbers 86-141)
  • Battle Action (From 19 November 1977 to 20 February 1982 - Numbers 142-363)
  • Battle (From 27 February 1982 to 1 October 1983 - Numbers 364-447)
  • Battle Action Force (From 8 October 1983 to 29 November 1986 - Numbers 448-612)
  • Battle (From 6 December 1986 to 17 January 1987 - Numbers 613-619)
  • Battle Storm Force (From 24 January 1987 to 23 January 1988 - Numbers 620-672)

* Editors might want to note that there was no issue on 30th December 1978 and issue 200 was issued a week later (6th January) potentially confusing people over the numbering if care isn't taken. Furthermore, there were two periods of industrial action that meant issues were delayed (issues from 19th January 1980 and 17th May 1980 were delayed, 8 issues being missed). This site has the correct number of issues - most other sources do not, including Wikipedia!
name: Battle Picture Weekly

description:
Superman's brilliant, brutal archnemesis Brainiac has forged an unholy alliance with one of the Man of Steel's greatest foes, and together they have set their sights on New Krypton -- and the tens of thousands of Kryptonian's who live there. Even as their technological terror rains from the skies, internal turmoil threatens to tear their target apart from within. 

But the fate of more than just New Krypton is at stake. Brainiac holds the people of countless worlds hostages on his ship. If they are not freed --- if Superman fails -- the future will cease to exist. 

Meanwhile, the ruthless General Zod will stop at nothing in his quest for vengeance against those who dare defy New Krypton -- and once he's through with Brainiac, the planet Earth is next on his hit list. 

Now Superman and a small band of his closest friends -- Supergirl, Superboy, Mon-El, and the Legion of Super-Heroes -- must fight to save their planets, their people, and their very lives. Will they stand together or fall forever?
name: Superman: Last Stand of New Krypton

description:
According to Indian legend, the mythical tribe of the Paumanoks bind the world of the Gods to those of nature and men. Luuna, daughter of the Great Sachem of the Paumanoks, is the victim of the curse of Unkui - the evil spirit of the night. He gave her two totems. The one is good and the other not, for on the nights of the full moon, Luuna is in the service of evil. Only the wizards of the great tribes of the south, past the deserts, can lift the curse. Follow Luuna on her quest and discover the magic of Indian mythology.

For the French version, see Luuna
name: Luuna
